193
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:29,783
Is it cloud based or over a network in-house?

194
00:11:31,164 --> 00:11:32,104
Oh, yeah, it's a combination.

195
00:11:32,645 --> 00:11:35,687
When we started, it was 100% cloud based because we

196
00:11:36,127 --> 00:11:39,350
just didn't have the time or the money to support

197
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,111
any kind of in-house server architecture

198
00:11:41,131 --> 00:11:45,214
or infrastructure, I should say.

199
00:11:45,274 --> 00:11:45,935
Now we have.

200
00:11:46,675 --> 00:11:49,457
So when we started, it was we used Amazon

201
00:11:49,477 --> 00:11:50,938
EC2 for hosting our.

202
00:11:53,102 --> 00:11:58,926
We use Perforce for source control and we use Jira for task tracking,

203
00:11:58,946 --> 00:12:00,547
which we adopted a little later.

204
00:12:01,828 --> 00:12:04,110
That was all in the Cloud.

205
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:09,153
And we use Slack, of course, sort of like everyone uses Slack nowadays.

206
00:12:09,574 --> 00:12:10,314
Sure.

207
00:12:11,415 --> 00:12:14,497
And that's all in the Cloud, and Slack itself is kind of a useful tool

208
00:12:14,517 --> 00:12:16,018
for just storing a huge amount of stuff.

209
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:27,657
Now that once we started to, like once we moved into an office and we had a team, a larger team on site that needed a lot higher bandwidth,

210
00:12:27,817 --> 00:12:36,141
the bottleneck between the office and the cloud, especially for source control access when you're moving quite a large amount of data,

211
00:12:37,081 --> 00:12:43,123
moving that for an entire local office through one external internet connection is kind of a big bottleneck.

212
00:12:43,243 --> 00:12:46,345
So we moved the Perforce server in-house.

213
00:12:46,953 --> 00:12:52,197
All of our source control, we have in-house servers now for our actual game content.

214
00:12:52,977 --> 00:12:58,982
But things like our production software in Slack and file sharing, all that stuff is

215
00:12:59,002 --> 00:13:05,767
still in the cloud, which enables people to work remotely a lot more easily.

216
00:13:06,327 --> 00:13:10,290
So I mean, I think working through the cloud is totally the best.

217
00:13:11,251 --> 00:13:11,951
easiest thing to do.

218
00:13:12,532 --> 00:13:14,634
And you should just keep doing it as long as you can.

219
00:13:14,654 --> 00:13:15,735
And for us,

220
00:13:15,755 --> 00:13:17,898
it just ultimately became just a technical limitation where

221
00:13:17,938 --> 00:13:23,884
it's still, you know, you really like if you need ten people

